        "id": 5395
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-07-08T12:04:27Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think this approach is very DRY, but has gone a bit too far in that readability has been hampered. serveJSON tries to do too much, I think.\n\nLet\u0027s look at how this code might look using something similar to sendJSONResponse used by Gold [1]\n\n    func (s *server) machinesHandler(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n      descriptions, err :\u003d s.store.List(r.Context())\n      if err !\u003d nil {\n        httputils.ReportError(w, err, \"Failed to read descriptions\", http.StatusInternalServerError)\n        return\n      }\n      sendJSONResponse(w, descriptions)\n    }\n\nBecause sendJSONResponse is assumed to be the last function call in a handler, it doesn\u0027t need to return an error for us to process and bail out early.\n\nThe `if err !\u003d nil ... httputils.ReportError` is repeated for each function call, but it\u0027s pretty standard Go code to do that sort of error checking as needed.\n\nI imagine y\u0027all will want to add tracing [2] [3] to the endpoints here to keep an eye on latency and bottlenecks. IMO, that should be added like:\n\n    func (s *server) machinesHandler(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n      ctx, span :\u003d trace.StartSpan(r.Context(), \"machinesHandler\")\n      defer span.End()\n      descriptions, err :\u003d s.store.List(ctx)\n      if err !\u003d nil {\n        httputils.ReportError(w, err, \"Failed to read descriptions\", http.StatusInternalServerError)\n        return\n      }\n      sendJSONResponse(w, descriptions)\n    }\n\nAgain, this is slightly duplicated for all handlers, but is very readable. I can\u0027t think of any ways to remove the duplication w/o dramatically hindering readability.\n\n[1] https://github.com/google/skia-buildbot/blob/a8b946c90d67aba23e1d11aa7e23ba3106b4d42b/golden/go/web/helpers.go#L36\n[2] https://cloud.google.com/trace\n[3] https://github.com/google/skia-buildbot/blob/a8b946c90d67aba23e1d11aa7e23ba3106b4d42b/golden/go/web/web.go#L580",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 171,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 171,
        "endChar": 10
      },
      "revId": "4fd9eef09ad23ad75316dede44c782b25cd2f9d1",
