      "writtenOn": "2021-07-08T16:52:21Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The anonymous func was pretty long and full of delimiters (and an additional comma); my intent was to make it easy to see where that ended. What if I had put `w` and \"Failed to read from datastore\" on the same line, separated by a comma? Would that be both idiomatic and readable?",
